# Getting current auth record in an event hook #4588 - GitHub
created: 2024-05-30, last updated: 2025-08-24, [Read more](https://github.com/pocketbase/pocketbase/discussions/4588)

You can read the auth state from the request context event field - `e.HttpContext`.
```
info := apis.RequestInfo(e.HttpContext)
admin := info.Admin // nil if not authenticated as admin
record := info.AuthRecord // nil if not authenticated as regular auth record
```
...
`OnRecordAfterCreateSuccess` doesn't have access to the request context.
Only the `*Request` suffixed hooks can access the request fields (see the note in https://pocketbase.io/docs/go-event-hooks/#record-model-hooks).
This is the same for both PocketBase v0.22 and v0.23+ (notice that the original question is asking for `OnRecordAfterCreateRequest`).
The v0.23+ `OnRecordAfterCreateRequest` equivalent hook is `OnRecordCreateRequest` with the user code executed after the `e.Next()` call:
```
app.OnRecordCreateRequest().BindFunc(func(e *core.RecordRequestEvent) error {
if err := e.Next(); err != nil {
return err
}
// e.App
// e.Record
// e.Auth and any other RequestEvent field (see https://pocketbase.io/docs/go-routing/)
return nil
})

# Hook order for API operations · pocketbase pocketbase · Discussion #6394
created: 2025-02-03, last updated: 2025-07-30, [Read more](https://github.com/pocketbase/pocketbase/discussions/6394)

Right now, I believe it is (for an update operation sent to the API) in that order:
- must validate against API rules of that collection
- OnRecordUpdateRequest
- OnRecordUpdate
- OnModelUpdate
- OnRecordValidate
- OnModelValidate
- OnRecordUpdateExecute
- OnModelUpdateExecute
- OnRecordAfterUpdateSuccess or OnRecordAfterUpdateError
- OnModelAfterUpdateSuccess or OnModelAfterUpdateError
…
...
}
...
No. The API rule is checked BEFORE the `OnRecordUpdateRequest` hook.
If the API rule fails then no hook is fired and it should result in 404 for this particular case.
...
This also applies to the other way around if I want to create a single notification that saves the creator of a game, I need to use the `OnRecordCreateRequest` because I can't access the `e.Auth` in other hooks:
...
Also, I assume that the other hooks are in sequences like this:
...
```
OnRecordCreateRequest {
OnRecordCreate {
OnRecordValidate {
}
OnRecordCreateExecute {
}
}
OnRecordAfterCreateSuccess {
}
OnRecordEnrich {
}
}
```

